# cvc5 -- SMT backend for pass/lec, used directly via its native C++ API. We use the
# official prebuilt non-GPL static libraries (no from-source solver build).
# Pinned to a tagged release (cvc5 >= 1.3.4 per lec.md). The bundled LGPL
# libgmp is intentionally NOT imported (see packages/cvc5.BUILD); GMP comes from
# the hermetic @gmp BCR module (bazel_dep above), not a system shared lib.
#
# The prebuilt is host-specific (we build `lhd` for the host, not cross-compile),
# so @cvc5 is registered by a module extension that picks the Linux x86_64 /
# macOS arm64 / ... asset matching the build host. Adding a platform is a one-row
# edit in packages/cvc5_repo.bzl; the repo name stays @cvc5 everywhere.
cvc5_ext = use_extension("//packages:cvc5_repo.bzl", "cvc5_repo")
use_repo(cvc5_ext, "cvc5")

# NOTE: @smtswitch and @pono were intentionally removed. pass/lec now talks to
# cvc5 directly through its native C++ API (it builds a combinational miter and
# discharges it with a single checkSat), so the solver-agnostic term layer
# (smt-switch) and the model-checking engine layer (pono, BMC/k-induction/IC3)
# are no longer needed. This also drops the fmt-12 source incompatibility and the
# rules_foreign_cc CMake build that those two carried. If unbounded *sequential*
# equivalence (no flop correspondence) is ever required, re-add pono here.

